events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson must make opponents miserable.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Brunson scores 41 points to lead the Knicks to a 113-109 victory over the Wizards

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 24 points and 14 rebounds, DeMar DeRozan scored 24 points against his former team and the Chicago Bulls beat the Toronto Raptors 116-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic and DeRozan each score 24 points to help Bulls beat Raptors 116-110

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points, Jalen Williams had 11 of his 27 points in the fourth quarter and the Oklahoma City Thunder snapped the Utah Jazz’s six-game winning streak with a 134-129 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander's 31 points and Jalen Williams' big fourth quarter carry Thunder past Jazz

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 26 of his 28 points in the second half and the West-leading Minnesota Timberwolves beat the injury-ravaged Memphis Grizzlies 118-103 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: West-leading Timberwolves beat Grizzlies 118-103 to reach midpoint with 30-11 record

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored 25 points and the short-handed Indiana Pacers held off the Sacramento Kings 126-121 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bennedict Mathurin scores 25 points, Pacers beat Kings 126-121
